cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.SI 

This paper is about the development of a new attack method for generating adversarial examples of Android malware that can evade machine learning based detectors. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also extensively discusses the use of machine learning models and their limitations, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category as well. Additionally, the paper proposes a new method for generating adversarial examples, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the need for automated tools to generate adversarial examples, which falls under the category of cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method using datasets used in previous studies, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
